answers.answer: How has your blood pressure been so far? Are you feeling light headed? Drink something with sugar in it and if you don't start to feel better relatively quickly I would give L&D a call.
No it's not normal, can be a sign of toxemia, if get checked out

Hey there hun. I'm a nurse, and trust me when I tell you, vision problems (especially that late in pregnancy) are not good. My first, and most important concern is your blood pressure, so definitely give your doc a call.

I have been dealing with early preeclampsia I'm 33 weeks. It sounds like your having high blood pressure and when you feel light headed you need to lie down on your left side it helps your blood pressure to lower. and make sure you contact your doctor to see what they would like for you to do far as going to the hospital or into the office for further testing.
